Morning, Thomas.

01:26:31.564 --> 01:26:35.091
- What happened?
- I had to leave.

01:26:35.168 --> 01:26:37.728
Did you hear everything?

01:26:37.804 --> 01:26:40.773
Yeah.

01:26:40.841 --> 01:26:43.435
Did you know?

01:26:43.510 --> 01:26:45.602
Did I know what?

01:26:45.678 --> 01:26:49.614
That she knew...
about your daughter.

01:27:00.525 --> 01:27:04.963
You know, when the,
when the police came to question me...

01:27:05.031 --> 01:27:08.797
they told me a lot of things.

01:27:08.868 --> 01:27:13.304
They told me that my wife was
having an affair with my brother;

01:27:13.372 --> 01:27:16.308
Had been for years.

01:27:16.376 --> 01:27:20.709
They told me that I thought
Lisa wasn't my daughter.

01:27:22.381 --> 01:27:25.647
They told me I thought she was Harold's.

01:27:25.717 --> 01:27:27.776
Wh-Why would they say that?

01:27:27.853 --> 01:27:32.416
Because they thought I could harm her...

01:27:32.492 --> 01:27:37.259
that I would harm her.

01:27:37.330 --> 01:27:43.098
And then they found the man
that... that did it.

01:27:43.168 --> 01:27:46.935
Let me go.

01:27:47.005 --> 01:27:51.101
And I went home.

01:27:53.846 --> 01:27:58.111
And then my wife was killed in a
car accident a couple months later.

01:27:58.184 --> 01:28:02.951
And Harold was in the car.

01:28:04.689 --> 01:28:07.750
He lived.

01:28:28.814 --> 01:28:30.907
What do you think it would have taken...

01:28:30.983 --> 01:28:34.418
for your father to kill someone?

01:28:34.486 --> 01:28:39.253
I'm asking because there's
someone that I want to kill now.

01:28:39.324 --> 01:28:44.763
I felt it last night as I
listened to him in the washroom.

01:28:44.830 --> 01:28:46.924
I don't understand.

01:28:46.999 --> 01:28:50.935
He set me up... to touch her.

01:28:51.003 --> 01:28:53.096
Why would he do that?

01:28:53.172 --> 01:28:57.768
He took something very special from me.

01:28:57.843 --> 01:29:01.939
I've had too many
special things taken away.

01:29:02.013 --> 01:29:06.951
- That's why we have to go back tonight.
- To kill him?

01:29:07.019 --> 01:29:09.309
What would you do, Thomas?
What would you do?

01:29:09.410 --> 01:29:10.112
Well...

01:29:10.188 --> 01:29:13.454
- Well, I would talk to him.
- I can't even get in there.

01:29:13.525 --> 01:29:16.461
What would you do?

01:29:16.529 --> 01:29:19.965
You go back tonight...

01:29:20.032 --> 01:29:22.626
and you have her dance for you...

01:29:22.702 --> 01:29:25.569
and then you touch her.

01:29:25.638 --> 01:29:28.300
And he'll throw you out
just like he threw me out.

01:29:28.374 --> 01:29:30.898
But I'll be waiting outside
with the gun.

01:29:30.976 --> 01:29:34.003
I'm not gonna help you kill somebody.

01:29:34.080 --> 01:29:37.345
Not even to save a few years in prison?

01:29:37.416 --> 01:29:39.646
No.

01:29:42.153 --> 01:29:44.416
Well, to help me then?

01:29:49.661 --> 01:29:53.096
And that was Mirella,
gentlemen. Mirella.

01:29:53.163 --> 01:29:56.599
You can have her at your own
table for only five dollars.

01:29:56.668 --> 01:29:58.931
Thank you, Mirella.

01:30:01.172 --> 01:30:06.268
And now, it's always a pleasure to
announce to you our next dancer.

01:30:06.344 --> 01:30:10.440
Gentlemen, please, let's give
a big round of applause...

01:30:10.514 --> 01:30:15.714
for Christina.

01:33:43.526 --> 01:33:47.122
Don't be afraid.

01:33:47.196 --> 01:33:49.722
I know everything about you.

01:33:49.799 --> 01:33:53.736
What do you know about me?

01:33:56.039 --> 01:33:59.769
I found her.

01:33:59.843 --> 01:34:03.778
You found who?

01:34:09.051 --> 01:34:11.645
Your little girl.

01:34:38.848 --> 01:34:41.044
I found her, man.

01:34:45.022 --> 01:34:46.955
I found her.

01:35:49.518 --> 01:35:53.454
Yeah, play something happy.
Play something happy.

01:35:53.521 --> 01:35:55.489
Yeah. Hello.

01:35:58.027 --> 01:36:00.460
Okay, I'll get it,
I'll get it, I'll get it.

01:36:07.202 --> 01:36:09.637
- Hi, Christina.
- Hi.

01:36:09.704 --> 01:36:14.972
- I'm a little bit early.
- Yeah, th-that's okay. Come on in.

01:36:19.949 --> 01:36:22.474
Yeah, I mean,
it's difficult for me to tell...

01:36:22.550 --> 01:36:25.315
'cause I never had much of a
musical education myself...

01:36:25.387 --> 01:36:28.481
but her teacher thinks
she's really talented.

01:36:28.556 --> 01:36:32.583
And actually, we were thinking
of buying her a better piano.

01:36:32.661 --> 01:36:35.597
An exotic baby grand, you know?

01:36:35.664 --> 01:36:37.929
And when I mentioned "baby grand,"
do you know what she said to me?

01:36:38.000 --> 01:36:42.436
She said, "Dad,
isn't that a contradiction in terms?"

01:36:42.505 --> 01:36:45.268
I mean, she just never
ceases to amaze me.

01:36:45.340 --> 01:36:47.275
I mean, she's eight years old.
Can you imagine?

01:36:47.342 --> 01:36:50.039
She can already identify-
Wh-What do you call that when...

01:36:50.112 --> 01:36:53.445
it's two words,
kind of cancel each other out?

01:36:53.516 --> 01:36:57.782
She just amazes me.

01:36:59.855 --> 01:37:04.621
Where's your mind?

01:37:04.693 --> 01:37:08.130
I was just thinking.

01:37:08.197 --> 01:37:11.462
About what?

01:37:11.534 --> 01:37:15.630
About the way you talk about Lisa.

01:37:15.704 --> 01:37:18.298
You get so excited.

01:37:18.373 --> 01:37:22.309
It's nice.

01:37:23.713 --> 01:37:27.443
Well, I'm sure your parents
talk about you that way too.

01:37:27.516 --> 01:37:30.576
I don't think so.

01:37:30.652 --> 01:37:34.418
Oh, I do.

01:37:34.489 --> 01:37:36.583
Why?

01:37:36.659 --> 01:37:40.925
Because you're a very
responsible young woman.

01:37:40.996 --> 01:37:45.434
Responsible to what?

01:37:45.501 --> 01:37:50.268
Well, to whatever it is
you believe you have to do.

01:37:50.338 --> 01:37:54.434
Like what?

01:37:54.509 --> 01:38:00.346
Well, Lisa loves it when you come
over to baby-sit, for example.

01:38:02.518 --> 01:38:06.283
She says you really listen to her.

01:38:06.354 --> 01:38:09.288
That's nice.

01:38:09.357 --> 01:38:12.053
She really listens to me too.

01:38:18.033 --> 01:38:21.093
She thinks you're not very happy.

01:38:21.169 --> 01:38:26.629
Listen, Christina,

01:38:26.707 --> 01:38:30.906
if there's, if there's ever
anything you want to talk about...

01:38:30.979 --> 01:38:34.506
about what might be going on
at home or whatever...

01:38:34.582 --> 01:38:39.417
you know that I'm here, okay?

01:38:41.321 --> 01:38:43.915
- Okay.
- Okay?

01:38:43.991 --> 01:38:46.084
Okay.

01:38:51.332 --> 01:38:54.926
Okay.

01:39:00.174 --> 01:39:03.406
Oh, no. It's okay.

01:39:06.513 --> 01:39:08.607
Thank you.

01:39:16.024 --> 01:39:19.551
You know, I really enjoy
these drives home, Mr. Brown.

01:39:19.627 --> 01:39:23.118
Good, good. So do I.

01:39:26.200 --> 01:39:29.067
- Bye, Mr. Brown.
- Good-bye.
